Only 2 Presidents in history have been impeached by the House. Both were later acquitted in he Senate. 

*Nixon resigned before he was impeached 

No President has ever been removed from office by impeachment and conviction.

The teacher in me is compelled to explain what this means

CIVICS 101:
Yesterday Congress announced a formal impeachment inquiry. 

This does not mean the President will be removed from office. 

This is just the beginning of a process that goes to the Senate pic.twitter.com/2hovzcaujf
